// WORK NIGHT //

In lieu of a workshop, we'll be having a work night. Show up when you can, work on a project or idea, and check off those to-do's.

There will be an opportunity at the top of the night to share some work (looking at you, Ludum Dare entries!).

Golisano Building / GOL / Building #70 - Room 2400

// DIRECTIONS //  Park in the J lot. The room is located on the second floor of the Golisano building (GOL or #70 on the map). After entering from the main doors on the J lot side, take the stairs in the atrium to the 2nd floor, turn left, and room 2400 is on the left immediately past the vending machines. Map for reference is below.

// WORKSHOP // Game balance utilizing mathematical models

// INSTRUCTOR // Ian Schreiber
Ian Schreiber has been in the industry for eight years, first as a programmer and then as a game designer. He has worked on five published game titles, including Playboy: the Mansion and the Nintendo DS version of Marvel Trading Card Game. He has also developed training/simulation games for two Fortune 500 companies. Ian has taught game design and development courses at Ohio University, Columbus State Community College, Savannah College of Art and Design, and currently at Rochester Institute of Technology and has mentored college students at those and several other universities. Ian is co-author of "Challenges for Game Designers."
